name: Dinengdeng
author: lola
summary: This flavorful vegetable dish comes from the Philippines and is cooked with bagoong (shrimp paste) and bangus (milkfish). Serve with rice.
ingredients: ½ pound long beans, cut into bite-size pieces
½ pound zucchini, cut into bite-size pieces
directions: Preheat an outdoor grill for medium heat and lightly oil the grate
Grill the milkfish fillets until the flesh flakes easily with a fork, 2 to 3 minutes per side
Combine the grilled fillets, tomato, onion, shrimp paste, and water to the pot; bring to a boil for 5 minutes
Add the long beans and zucchini; stir
Cover the pot and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes
Stir the okra into the mixture and cook another 5 minutes
